1
00:00:00,083 --> 00:00:01,450
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,450 --> 00:00:02,783
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:04,683 --> 00:00:07,450
You said you had something to tell me.
Go ahead.

4
00:00:08,583 --> 00:00:09,650
Grandpa, I...

5
00:00:10,750 --> 00:00:13,450
I'm going to move out.

6
00:00:15,183 --> 00:00:18,150
What? Move out?

7
00:00:20,650 --> 00:00:21,650
Do you really...

8
00:00:23,383 --> 00:00:24,950
not understand what I want?

9
00:00:25,983 --> 00:00:28,550
Why do you think I asked you to come back
and made you compete?

10
00:00:29,050 --> 00:00:31,650
I do. That's why I want to leave.

11
00:00:32,150 --> 00:00:33,850
What do you mean?

12
00:00:34,383 --> 00:00:36,150
You say you understand me,
yet you want to move out?

13
00:00:37,250 --> 00:00:38,250
Gyeol.

14
00:00:38,950 --> 00:00:40,150
I'm sorry, Grandma.

15
00:00:40,783 --> 00:00:43,650
Grandpa, I lost the first round,

16
00:00:43,650 --> 00:00:44,883
but regardless of the result,

17
00:00:44,883 --> 00:00:47,650
I really want to make
this retirement community project succeed.

18
00:00:48,050 --> 00:00:51,050
Are you saying you can't do that
while living here?

19
00:00:51,650 --> 00:00:53,350
I found a neighborhood that matches...

20
00:00:53,350 --> 00:00:55,883
the kind of retirement community
I envision.

21
00:00:56,550 --> 00:00:58,850
So I want to live there myself...

22
00:00:58,850 --> 00:01:01,350
and see if my idea is right.

23
00:01:03,083 --> 00:01:05,050
Is that really all?

24
00:01:07,750 --> 00:01:09,550
That's not all, but...

25
00:01:11,050 --> 00:01:12,483
Please allow it, Grandpa.

26
00:01:12,950 --> 00:01:14,850
Can't you reconsider?

27
00:01:15,750 --> 00:01:19,683
Don't you understand how much
your grandpa wants you by his side?

28
00:01:20,150 --> 00:01:21,650
I'll visit often, Grandma.

29
00:01:21,983 --> 00:01:24,550
I'll come by often, have meals,
and even stay over.

30
00:01:26,883 --> 00:01:28,550
If that's truly your decision,

31
00:01:29,583 --> 00:01:31,250
there's no way to stop you.

32
00:01:31,250 --> 00:01:32,983
Honey.

33
00:01:33,950 --> 00:01:37,650
What can we do? He's made up his mind.

34
00:01:40,883 --> 00:01:42,750
The night view is amazing, right?

35
00:01:44,350 --> 00:01:46,783
You must be exhausted
after running around all day.

36
00:01:46,950 --> 00:01:50,250
Korean fine dining, a tea house,
and even a movie theater...

37
00:01:50,950 --> 00:01:52,750
I get that those are all work-related,

38
00:01:53,250 --> 00:01:56,583
but was a walk along the Hangang River
part of our retirement community plan?

39
00:01:56,950 --> 00:01:58,150
Why not?

40
00:01:58,383 --> 00:02:00,950
If the person in charge tries it first...

41
00:02:00,950 --> 00:02:04,250
and says it works,
we can include it in the program.

42
00:02:19,483 --> 00:02:22,283
Gyeol having a birthday party
surprised me too.

43
00:02:23,883 --> 00:02:27,283
He used to hate
even hearing the words "happy birthday."

44
00:02:29,050 --> 00:02:31,483
And to think Ms. Cho Eun Ae
opened the door...

45
00:02:32,350 --> 00:02:34,350
that had been shut for 25 years in one go.

46
00:02:35,250 --> 00:02:38,350
Yes, that was quite a punch.

47
00:02:39,683 --> 00:02:40,850
If nothing else,

48
00:02:41,483 --> 00:02:43,750
I thought his birthday was off-limits.

49
00:02:53,350 --> 00:02:54,350
Seo Seung Ri,

50
00:02:56,350 --> 00:02:58,050
do you even know when my birthday is?

51
00:03:01,950 --> 00:03:04,283
Then again, of course you don't.

52
00:03:05,550 --> 00:03:07,083
Your mind is always full of...

53
00:03:14,550 --> 00:03:17,683
Want some ramyeon?

54
00:03:19,983 --> 00:03:21,850
You can't come to the Hangang River
and not have ramyeon.

55
00:03:22,650 --> 00:03:23,650
Just wait a bit.

56
00:03:37,383 --> 00:03:38,450
This is really good.

57
00:03:43,350 --> 00:03:44,350
Seung Ri,

58
00:03:45,683 --> 00:03:48,083
you don't know when I first fell for you,
do you?

59
00:03:50,183 --> 00:03:51,750
Are you trying to give me indigestion?

60
00:03:52,083 --> 00:03:53,083
Aren't you curious...

61
00:03:53,750 --> 00:03:56,450
about how I ended up
becoming a Seo Seung Ri zombie?

62
00:03:59,850 --> 00:04:01,950
I think I was about 15.

63
00:04:04,183 --> 00:04:07,650
I got scolded badly by Grandpa
for picking on Gyeol...

64
00:04:08,750 --> 00:04:10,483
and was crying alone in the garden...

65
00:04:12,350 --> 00:04:14,583
when you took me to your house
in the annex...

66
00:04:14,883 --> 00:04:16,050
and made me ramyeon.

67
00:04:17,783 --> 00:04:21,283
My mom never let me eat instant food,

68
00:04:21,883 --> 00:04:24,050
so that was the first time
I ever had ramyeon.

69
00:04:25,850 --> 00:04:28,850
It tasted like paradise.

70
00:04:30,350 --> 00:04:33,650
But I was wolfing it down so much...

71
00:04:33,650 --> 00:04:35,150
that I must've looked pitiful,

72
00:04:36,150 --> 00:04:37,883
so you quietly slid your bowl...

73
00:04:37,883 --> 00:04:40,450
over to me...

74
00:04:40,950 --> 00:04:43,050
and said, "Eat mine too."

75
00:04:46,083 --> 00:04:48,083
I was so embarrassed back then.

76
00:04:50,050 --> 00:04:52,983
I must've looked like a pig to you, right?

77
00:04:56,083 --> 00:04:57,250
You laughed just now!

78
00:05:00,050 --> 00:05:01,983
Did you know that's the first time
you've smiled today?

79
00:05:03,750 --> 00:05:06,950
Anyway, from that day on,

80
00:05:07,450 --> 00:05:08,950
I became your prisoner.

81
00:05:10,250 --> 00:05:13,050
Five years, ten years...

82
00:05:13,950 --> 00:05:15,350
passed like that,

83
00:05:17,450 --> 00:05:19,150
but your feelings never changed,

84
00:05:20,050 --> 00:05:22,350
and mine didn't either.

85
00:05:25,350 --> 00:05:28,350
If it's been so long,
it's about time to end it.

86
00:05:30,150 --> 00:05:33,650
You know better than anyone
that words like that don't work.

87
00:05:36,783 --> 00:05:37,783
Right.

88
00:05:39,450 --> 00:05:40,683
Here, a gift.

89
00:05:41,450 --> 00:05:43,283
What is this?

90
00:05:43,383 --> 00:05:46,283
I saw it while picking out ramyeon,
so I bought one.

91
00:05:47,083 --> 00:05:48,483
I didn't just pick it up on the way, okay?

92
00:05:49,383 --> 00:05:51,650
Give me your arm. There.

93
00:05:59,450 --> 00:06:02,350
I'm better now, so we should head home.

94
00:06:02,350 --> 00:06:05,683
Manager Seo, are you rich or something?

95
00:06:06,583 --> 00:06:09,550
How can you leave this much ramyeon?

96
00:06:10,550 --> 00:06:11,683
You're spoiled.

97
00:06:11,683 --> 00:06:13,683
You barely ate anything.

98
00:06:21,983 --> 00:06:23,183
Nice.

99
00:06:26,283 --> 00:06:29,583
What are they even talking about in there?
It's been 30 minutes.

100
00:06:31,583 --> 00:06:33,550
Should I sneak over and eavesdrop?

101
00:06:33,850 --> 00:06:35,050
I'm pretty good at that.

102
00:06:35,250 --> 00:06:36,550
Seriously.

103
00:06:36,550 --> 00:06:38,783
What did I tell you? You should...

104
00:06:38,783 --> 00:06:39,950
All right.

105
00:06:40,483 --> 00:06:43,450
I'll act with dignity like the future head
of the great Kangsu Group's wife.

106
00:06:44,650 --> 00:06:45,783
Silly you.

107
00:06:46,750 --> 00:06:48,583
You're done talking?

108
00:06:49,050 --> 00:06:50,683
Come sit here, Gyeol.

109
00:06:50,683 --> 00:06:51,683
Yes.

110
00:06:52,683 --> 00:06:53,683
Okay.

111
00:06:58,750 --> 00:07:01,250
What did you talk about for so long?

112
00:07:02,550 --> 00:07:05,183
You're not contesting the results,
are you?

113
00:07:05,683 --> 00:07:07,283
No, it's nothing like that.

114
00:07:08,183 --> 00:07:10,750
Father, I'm planning to move out soon.

115
00:07:11,050 --> 00:07:12,383
I got Grandpa's permission.

116
00:07:12,983 --> 00:07:14,650
What? Move out?

117
00:07:15,650 --> 00:07:17,750
You mean you're going to leave this house?

118
00:07:17,983 --> 00:07:19,050
Yes, Mother.

119
00:07:20,250 --> 00:07:23,050
And Grandpa allowed it?

120
00:07:23,483 --> 00:07:26,450
Yes. Father, Mother,
you'll allow it too, right?

121
00:07:27,550 --> 00:07:29,150
Well, I...

122
00:07:31,050 --> 00:07:33,550
In this house, your grandpa's word is law,

123
00:07:34,383 --> 00:07:35,950
so what does our permission matter?

124
00:07:36,850 --> 00:07:38,650
So where are you planning to go?

125
00:07:38,850 --> 00:07:41,083
Some studio near your workplace?

126
00:07:41,083 --> 00:07:42,350
That sounds good.

127
00:07:42,350 --> 00:07:44,650
You don't drive,
so commuting would be easier.

128
00:07:45,650 --> 00:07:46,883
When are you moving out?

129
00:07:47,583 --> 00:07:50,283
Soon.
I'll move out as quickly as possible.

130
00:07:50,883 --> 00:07:52,050
I'll head upstairs now.

131
00:07:52,550 --> 00:07:53,850
Okay.

132
00:07:53,850 --> 00:07:56,350
Go rest.

133
00:07:59,650 --> 00:08:00,950
What's gotten into him all of a sudden?

134
00:08:01,783 --> 00:08:02,850
Is it because of me?

135
00:08:03,650 --> 00:08:06,050
I don't think I made it that obvious
that I don't like him.

136
00:08:06,250 --> 00:08:08,183
Do you think he noticed
we went through his room?

137
00:08:08,950 --> 00:08:11,050
Or maybe he's avoiding us...

138
00:08:11,050 --> 00:08:13,783
so he can face Min Ho properly?

139
00:08:15,550 --> 00:08:16,550
I'm home.

140
00:08:16,783 --> 00:08:18,950
Min Ho, big news.

141
00:08:18,983 --> 00:08:20,350
What? Big news?

142
00:08:23,183 --> 00:08:24,183
Come in.

143
00:08:26,383 --> 00:08:28,983
What do you mean you're moving out
all of a sudden?

144
00:08:29,750 --> 00:08:31,850
It means exactly that. I'm moving out.

145
00:08:32,150 --> 00:08:33,150
Why?

146
00:08:33,150 --> 00:08:35,550
Why else? People our age usually move out.

147
00:08:36,583 --> 00:08:39,050
Aren't you moving out? You're old enough.

148
00:08:39,950 --> 00:08:40,950
Whatever.

149
00:08:41,850 --> 00:08:44,183
Something's changed with you.

150
00:08:44,783 --> 00:08:47,150
Did something happen with Ms. Cho Eun Ae?

151
00:08:47,450 --> 00:08:49,150
Why are you bringing her into this?

152
00:08:49,150 --> 00:08:51,350
What does my moving out
have to do with her?

153
00:08:51,550 --> 00:08:53,650
Fine, let's say it doesn't matter.

154
00:08:54,950 --> 00:08:56,950
How long are you
going to leave Seung Ri like that?

155
00:08:59,150 --> 00:09:01,450
You know you're the only one...

156
00:09:01,450 --> 00:09:03,150
who can make her move on, right?

157
00:09:05,350 --> 00:09:08,350
All right, I get what you mean.
I'll take care of it.

158
00:09:09,350 --> 00:09:11,683
Have you found a place yet?

159
00:09:11,850 --> 00:09:12,850
I will soon.

160
00:09:14,383 --> 00:09:15,650
Okay, get some rest.

161
00:09:16,350 --> 00:09:18,350
Right. You punk.

162
00:09:19,350 --> 00:09:22,483
If you're going to have a birthday party,
at least clean up the evidence.

163
00:09:23,083 --> 00:09:24,083
What?

164
00:09:25,050 --> 00:09:28,250
Never mind. It works out for me.

165
00:09:29,350 --> 00:09:31,050
Happy belated birthday.

166
00:09:45,883 --> 00:09:48,550
Not bad for our first matching item.

167
00:09:57,650 --> 00:09:59,450
But your feelings never changed,

168
00:10:00,283 --> 00:10:02,450
and mine didn't either.

169
00:10:04,283 --> 00:10:07,250
If it's been so long,
it's about time to end it.

170
00:10:07,850 --> 00:10:11,250
You know better than anyone
that words like that don't work.

171
00:10:27,450 --> 00:10:29,750
Find a common denominator?

172
00:10:31,250 --> 00:10:33,850
Don't tell me you don't know how?

173
00:10:36,750 --> 00:10:38,950
You make the denominators the same.

174
00:10:39,650 --> 00:10:40,750
The same denominator?

175
00:10:42,450 --> 00:10:44,150
I'm sure I used to know this.

176
00:10:44,750 --> 00:10:47,050
Mom, didn't you say
you were really good at school?

177
00:10:47,383 --> 00:10:51,283
You said you couldn't pass down wealth,
but at least we inherited your brains.

178
00:10:51,750 --> 00:10:54,150
Just wait till you're my age.

179
00:10:54,150 --> 00:10:56,950
I can't even remember
what I ate last night,

180
00:10:57,150 --> 00:11:00,650
and you expect me
to remember something from decades ago?

181
00:11:00,650 --> 00:11:02,483
Still,

182
00:11:02,650 --> 00:11:05,650
with basics like this,
how are you going to prepare for the CSAT?

183
00:11:05,783 --> 00:11:09,083
Are you scolding me
for not knowing the basics?

184
00:11:09,150 --> 00:11:10,150
I'm not doing this.

185
00:11:10,250 --> 00:11:13,983
What do you mean you're not?
Do you think I'm making you study for me?

186
00:11:14,250 --> 00:11:17,150
It's for your own life!

187
00:11:17,683 --> 00:11:19,483
You little...

188
00:11:21,950 --> 00:11:25,150
Watch closely, okay? Hold your pencil.

189
00:11:26,450 --> 00:11:28,250
To make the denominators the same...

190
00:11:28,483 --> 00:11:30,583
Are you watching, Mom?

191
00:11:31,550 --> 00:11:34,350
Seriously, it's just common denominators.

192
00:11:34,383 --> 00:11:37,183
Did she know it from birth or something?

193
00:11:37,783 --> 00:11:38,783
What's wrong?

194
00:11:39,583 --> 00:11:41,350
Eun Nim scolded me,

195
00:11:41,350 --> 00:11:43,550
saying my math basics are terrible.

196
00:11:43,883 --> 00:11:46,350
Eun Nim scolded you? That little...

197
00:11:46,350 --> 00:11:47,850
It's fine.

198
00:11:48,450 --> 00:11:51,050
I know you can only be sweet
with the kids.

199
00:11:53,350 --> 00:11:57,250
By the way, no one's rented the room yet.

200
00:11:58,050 --> 00:11:59,583
No one even came to see it?

201
00:12:00,550 --> 00:12:03,583
A few people came by,
but no one called back.

202
00:12:04,283 --> 00:12:05,750
Should we lower the rent?

203
00:12:10,150 --> 00:12:11,150
Hello?

204
00:12:13,750 --> 00:12:15,183
Are you calling about the rental ad?

205
00:12:16,350 --> 00:12:18,150
Yes, it's still available,

206
00:12:18,950 --> 00:12:20,283
but due to our situation,

207
00:12:20,583 --> 00:12:23,150
we're looking for a female tenant.

208
00:12:23,883 --> 00:12:26,950
Really? Is there a specific reason?

209
00:12:27,150 --> 00:12:29,783
The room is on the same floor
as our daughters',

210
00:12:29,950 --> 00:12:31,850
so it might be uncomfortable.

211
00:12:32,583 --> 00:12:34,050
That won't be an issue.

212
00:12:34,350 --> 00:12:37,383
I come home late and leave early,

213
00:12:37,683 --> 00:12:39,450
so we won't run into each other much.

214
00:12:40,050 --> 00:12:42,783
Really? Then would you like
to come see the room tomorrow?

215
00:12:44,483 --> 00:12:46,450
If possible,
I'd like to sign the contract right away.

216
00:12:47,183 --> 00:12:49,683
What? Without even seeing the room?

217
00:12:50,350 --> 00:12:53,650
Yes, I saw the photos online,
and it looks clean.

218
00:12:54,183 --> 00:12:56,183
You'll still need to sign the contract,

219
00:12:57,150 --> 00:13:00,150
so please bring your ID
and come to the real estate office.

220
00:13:01,083 --> 00:13:04,050
Could we do it electronically instead?

221
00:13:04,683 --> 00:13:08,450
Sorry? Yes, that's possible.

222
00:13:09,050 --> 00:13:12,550
Also, I have one request.

223
00:13:12,850 --> 00:13:15,583
Would a short-term lease
of about four months be okay?

224
00:13:15,950 --> 00:13:19,450
Four months? That should be fine.

225
00:13:20,350 --> 00:13:21,450
Thank you.

226
00:13:21,483 --> 00:13:24,750
When can I move in?
I'd prefer as soon as possible.

227
00:13:25,583 --> 00:13:28,750
All right, we can arrange that.

228
00:13:31,950 --> 00:13:33,350
What on earth is going on?

229
00:13:33,350 --> 00:13:36,450
Signing without even seeing the place?

230
00:13:37,250 --> 00:13:39,650
It sounded like a man.
You should've said no.

231
00:13:39,650 --> 00:13:41,183
The girls will be uncomfortable.

232
00:13:41,550 --> 00:13:42,750
I was going to,

233
00:13:42,750 --> 00:13:44,983
but he wanted to sign right away,
so I just went along with it.

234
00:13:46,750 --> 00:13:48,150
Let's just do it.

235
00:13:48,350 --> 00:13:50,683
It's not like anyone else is lining up.

236
00:13:52,250 --> 00:13:53,483
Will this really be okay?

237
00:13:53,783 --> 00:13:56,850
Our daughters won't feel uncomfortable
just because it's a male tenant.

238
00:13:57,150 --> 00:13:58,983
If anything,
he'd be the one feeling uncomfortable.

239
00:13:59,883 --> 00:14:00,950
I'm back.

240
00:14:00,950 --> 00:14:02,850
Hey. Did you go work out?

241
00:14:02,983 --> 00:14:04,450
Yes, Dad. I'll head upstairs.

242
00:14:04,450 --> 00:14:07,650
Cho Eun Ae, move your stuff
to Eun Nim's room right now.

243
00:14:07,950 --> 00:14:10,083
- What?
- I just rented the room.

244
00:14:10,083 --> 00:14:12,283
He wants to move in as soon as possible,
so hurry.

245
00:14:12,283 --> 00:14:13,650
Mom.

246
00:14:13,650 --> 00:14:17,250
I haven't even agreed yet.
How can you do this?

247
00:14:17,350 --> 00:14:19,583
Your agreement aside,
let's get the facts straight.

248
00:14:19,950 --> 00:14:22,650
You're not the owner of this house.
Your dad is.

249
00:14:23,750 --> 00:14:27,050
I'm sorry, Eun Ae.
Your mom is very firm about this.

250
00:14:28,283 --> 00:14:32,150
My goal is to grow old
without relying on you kids...

251
00:14:32,283 --> 00:14:34,183
and live on our own.

252
00:14:34,950 --> 00:14:36,150
So we have no choice.

253
00:14:37,850 --> 00:14:39,050
What are you doing? Hurry.

254
00:14:43,483 --> 00:14:44,650
- Rock, paper, scissors.
- Rock, paper, scissors.

255
00:14:44,650 --> 00:14:46,383
- Rock, paper, scissors.
- Rock, paper, scissors. Yes!

256
00:14:46,383 --> 00:14:47,950
- The bed is mine today.
- No way.

257
00:14:47,950 --> 00:14:49,283
Let's do it again. Best out of three.

258
00:14:49,283 --> 00:14:51,850
Are you kidding me? You said one round.

259
00:14:51,850 --> 00:14:54,750
When did I say that?
Koreans always do best of three.

260
00:14:55,383 --> 00:14:57,450
Get down already.

261
00:14:57,683 --> 00:14:59,350
Seriously.

262
00:14:59,650 --> 00:15:01,150
Don't you know how to respect your elders?

263
00:15:01,550 --> 00:15:03,550
You're younger, so you should sleep here.

264
00:15:04,383 --> 00:15:05,450
This is nice.

265
00:15:08,050 --> 00:15:10,883
It's been a while since we shared a room.
It brings back memories.

266
00:15:11,650 --> 00:15:14,083
You used to cry
and refuse to sleep without me...

267
00:15:14,083 --> 00:15:16,450
when you were little,
you little snot-nosed kid.

268
00:15:17,350 --> 00:15:19,383
That was ages ago.

269
00:15:20,150 --> 00:15:23,250
When I was in school,
you snored so loudly.

270
00:15:23,250 --> 00:15:25,450
Do you know how much
I suffered from lack of sleep?

271
00:15:25,750 --> 00:15:27,783
Hey, I don't snore.

272
00:15:27,783 --> 00:15:30,450
Just turn off the lights, and don't snore.

273
00:15:33,550 --> 00:15:36,350
You still cling to those comic books?

274
00:15:36,550 --> 00:15:38,683
Throw them away. The room's already tiny.

275
00:15:38,983 --> 00:15:40,450
Don't you dare.

276
00:15:40,950 --> 00:15:44,383
Those books are what led me, Cho Eun Nim,
to become a writer.

277
00:15:44,383 --> 00:15:46,350
They're my source of inspiration.

278
00:15:59,683 --> 00:16:01,083
Mom said...

279
00:16:02,950 --> 00:16:04,950
her goal is to grow old...

280
00:16:04,950 --> 00:16:08,350
without relying on us.

281
00:16:10,550 --> 00:16:11,850
They've devoted...

282
00:16:12,883 --> 00:16:15,083
their whole lives to us.

283
00:16:16,850 --> 00:16:18,450
How can they keep thinking only of us
till the end?

284
00:16:21,183 --> 00:16:22,183
So you moved rooms...

285
00:16:23,150 --> 00:16:25,350
without complaining?

286
00:16:26,350 --> 00:16:28,083
There was nothing to argue about.

287
00:16:30,783 --> 00:16:34,050
Do you think we could do the same
when we become parents?

288
00:16:34,383 --> 00:16:37,650
I'm not so sure.

289
00:16:41,350 --> 00:16:42,350
Is your back uncomfortable?

290
00:16:42,950 --> 00:16:44,650
Why? Are you giving me the bed?

291
00:16:54,883 --> 00:16:57,083
(Kangsu Construction)

292
00:16:57,350 --> 00:16:59,383
About having Joy
start conversations first,

293
00:16:59,650 --> 00:17:01,783
wouldn't users feel uncomfortable?

294
00:17:02,750 --> 00:17:04,683
Of course, it's good...

295
00:17:04,683 --> 00:17:06,550
to respond only when users want,

296
00:17:06,850 --> 00:17:09,483
but when you live alone,
there's no one to talk to.

297
00:17:09,750 --> 00:17:12,050
If Joy starts the conversation...

298
00:17:12,650 --> 00:17:14,850
It feels like
you're interacting with someone?

299
00:17:15,650 --> 00:17:17,950
Right. Of course, this feature...

300
00:17:17,950 --> 00:17:19,750
will be refined in various ways...

301
00:17:19,750 --> 00:17:21,283
based on user feedback.

302
00:17:21,750 --> 00:17:24,550
Good.
Mr. Kim, do you have any other opinions?

303
00:17:24,950 --> 00:17:26,450
I think it's good.

304
00:17:27,250 --> 00:17:29,650
All right. It's almost lunchtime,

305
00:17:29,650 --> 00:17:31,983
so let's wrap up the meeting.
I'm taking a half day this afternoon.

306
00:17:32,383 --> 00:17:34,683
- What? Again?
- Yes.

307
00:17:45,350 --> 00:17:48,583
How about reviewing the details
before approving things?

308
00:17:50,083 --> 00:17:51,083
Review the details?

309
00:17:52,250 --> 00:17:54,083
What, are you saying I'm signing things...

310
00:17:54,083 --> 00:17:55,350
without knowing anything?

311
00:17:55,950 --> 00:17:57,150
That's not what I meant,

312
00:17:57,850 --> 00:18:00,650
but I noticed there are some expenses...

313
00:18:01,083 --> 00:18:04,883
not directly related to the project
in the finance documents you just signed.

314
00:18:05,150 --> 00:18:06,250
What do you mean?

315
00:18:06,250 --> 00:18:08,650
What expenses aren't related?

316
00:18:08,650 --> 00:18:11,283
Which ones?

317
00:18:11,750 --> 00:18:13,350
I'll look into it precisely.

318
00:18:14,683 --> 00:18:16,250
Are you saying I can't even track...

319
00:18:16,250 --> 00:18:18,650
improper fund flows?

320
00:18:19,783 --> 00:18:23,150
That's not it,
but I thought you should be more careful.

321
00:18:24,650 --> 00:18:27,250
No matter how capable you were at Samho,

322
00:18:27,250 --> 00:18:29,350
this is Kangsu Construction.

323
00:18:30,350 --> 00:18:32,083
What are you trying to prove?

324
00:18:32,683 --> 00:18:35,250
- You may go.
- Yes.

325
00:18:36,250 --> 00:18:37,250
Leave it.

326
00:18:43,850 --> 00:18:45,883
What is with that guy?

327
00:18:46,550 --> 00:18:49,950
He saw all that in a minute?

328
00:18:49,950 --> 00:18:50,950
How?

329
00:18:58,350 --> 00:19:00,850
Director of Finance, it's me.

330
00:19:01,650 --> 00:19:04,550
We need to have lunch together today.

331
00:19:20,450 --> 00:19:23,050
What is it? What's wrong?

332
00:19:24,550 --> 00:19:25,583
Nothing.

333
00:19:26,683 --> 00:19:28,983
CEO Ko isn't easy, is he?

334
00:19:29,750 --> 00:19:30,750
Right.

335
00:19:31,783 --> 00:19:34,350
By the way, the Chairman still has
a lot on his plate, doesn't he?

336
00:19:35,050 --> 00:19:37,750
Even though he's at home,
he hasn't stepped away from work.

337
00:19:46,383 --> 00:19:50,150
Yes, sir. You're heading out for lunch?

338
00:19:50,783 --> 00:19:51,783
Then I'll...

339
00:19:51,783 --> 00:19:55,250
No, don't worry about it.
Go eat on your own.

340
00:19:55,650 --> 00:19:57,150
Yes, have a good day.

341
00:20:01,950 --> 00:20:04,983
Hey, Eun Ae.
You want to grab lunch with me?

342
00:20:06,583 --> 00:20:08,883
That place from last time? Okay.

343
00:20:09,550 --> 00:20:10,683
I'll see you in the lobby soon.

344
00:20:11,850 --> 00:20:14,050
- Your daughter works here?
- Yeah.

345
00:20:15,150 --> 00:20:17,050
I guess I hadn't told you.

346
00:20:17,450 --> 00:20:19,150
She's an intern in Planning.

347
00:20:19,150 --> 00:20:22,150
What? My daughter's in Planning too.

348
00:20:23,383 --> 00:20:26,550
Wait, then Manager Seo...

349
00:20:26,750 --> 00:20:27,750
You know my daughter?

350
00:20:27,750 --> 00:20:29,850
Yeah, when she first joined,

351
00:20:29,850 --> 00:20:32,050
she kept bragging
about how nice her supervisor was.

352
00:20:32,450 --> 00:20:33,850
That was Manager Seo.

353
00:20:35,883 --> 00:20:37,350
What a coincidence.

354
00:20:38,350 --> 00:20:40,750
Since we're talking about it,
should we eat with our daughters?

355
00:20:40,950 --> 00:20:43,150
Sure, I'll call her.

356
00:20:45,550 --> 00:20:48,950
I can't believe
your father is friends with my father.

357
00:20:49,250 --> 00:20:51,683
I never would've imagined it.

358
00:20:52,350 --> 00:20:53,350
Me neither.

359
00:20:53,583 --> 00:20:57,083
Come to think of it, weren't you the one
protesting in the lobby?

360
00:20:58,450 --> 00:20:59,483
You saw that?

361
00:20:59,650 --> 00:21:02,750
That's my dark past. Can you forget it?

362
00:21:06,150 --> 00:21:07,283
- Mr. Seo.
- Hey.

363
00:21:08,183 --> 00:21:09,783
- Here for lunch?
- Yes.

364
00:21:10,283 --> 00:21:12,150
- Team Manager Ko's here too.
- Yes.

365
00:21:13,250 --> 00:21:14,383
Mind if we join you?

366
00:21:14,383 --> 00:21:15,383
- No.
- No.

367
00:21:16,350 --> 00:21:17,550
Team Manager, please sit.

368
00:21:17,783 --> 00:21:18,883
Okay.

369
00:21:27,850 --> 00:21:29,350
I thought you were taking a half day.

370
00:21:29,350 --> 00:21:30,583
I'll eat first.

371
00:21:41,050 --> 00:21:43,283
Is this what they call fate?

372
00:21:43,583 --> 00:21:45,050
Three fathers who are friends,

373
00:21:45,050 --> 00:21:47,850
and their children all working
at the same company.

374
00:21:48,983 --> 00:21:50,750
I don't know about fate,

375
00:21:51,350 --> 00:21:52,883
but it's definitely
not an ordinary connection.

376
00:21:53,050 --> 00:21:56,083
Exactly. And Team Manager Ko
and Ms. Cho Eun Ae...

377
00:21:56,083 --> 00:21:58,583
have amazing teamwork these days.

378
00:22:01,250 --> 00:22:02,250
Are you okay?

379
00:22:02,750 --> 00:22:04,650
Yes, I'm fine.

380
00:22:04,983 --> 00:22:07,350
See? Perfect teamwork.

381
00:22:09,850 --> 00:22:11,583
Manager Seo,
you like cucumber kimchi, right?

382
00:22:13,350 --> 00:22:14,483
I'm done eating.

383
00:22:15,583 --> 00:22:18,783
You barely ate half a bowl.
Have a bit more.

384
00:22:34,383 --> 00:22:36,550
Yes, I received the contract.

385
00:22:36,850 --> 00:22:39,850
You can transfer the payment
on move-in day.

386
00:22:40,950 --> 00:22:41,950
Yes.

387
00:22:47,450 --> 00:22:49,150
(Ko Gyeol has deposited 10,500 dollars
in your account.)

388
00:22:50,950 --> 00:22:52,250
Why is he in such a hurry?

389
00:22:54,850 --> 00:22:57,150
What is it? Did someone rent the room?

390
00:22:57,583 --> 00:23:01,350
Yes, the person who called last night...

391
00:23:01,350 --> 00:23:04,183
already sent the deposit...

392
00:23:04,183 --> 00:23:05,650
and one month's rent.

393
00:23:06,750 --> 00:23:08,250
That's great.

394
00:23:08,250 --> 00:23:10,850
You were worried about it not renting.

395
00:23:15,183 --> 00:23:16,683
Why the sigh?

396
00:23:17,050 --> 00:23:20,850
Business is going well.
You should be happy.

397
00:23:21,450 --> 00:23:23,783
Even if business is good,

398
00:23:23,783 --> 00:23:27,783
it's not like I can fully appreciate it
at this age.

399
00:23:30,650 --> 00:23:31,783
How's your studying going?

400
00:23:35,883 --> 00:23:36,883
Hello?

401
00:23:38,450 --> 00:23:40,983
What? Today?

402
00:23:41,583 --> 00:23:43,150
- This way.
- Yes.

403
00:23:44,650 --> 00:23:47,050
Is that all your luggage?

404
00:23:47,250 --> 00:23:49,383
Yes, I had to move out in a hurry.

405
00:23:49,650 --> 00:23:51,550
I'll just bring this for today.

406
00:23:51,650 --> 00:23:53,050
Come in.

407
00:23:53,050 --> 00:23:54,483
- I'll show you the room.
- Okay.

408
00:24:00,650 --> 00:24:02,050
- This way.
- Yes.

409
00:24:02,150 --> 00:24:04,450
This used to be my daughter's room.

410
00:24:05,383 --> 00:24:06,850
The furniture might not be great.

411
00:24:07,450 --> 00:24:09,250
It's fine. It's only for four months.

412
00:24:09,783 --> 00:24:12,383
The bedding is new,
so feel free to use it.

413
00:24:12,383 --> 00:24:14,483
The bathroom is right next door.

414
00:24:15,050 --> 00:24:16,050
Yes.

415
00:24:16,050 --> 00:24:17,850
All right, unpack and rest.

416
00:24:17,850 --> 00:24:19,050
- Thank you.
- Sure.

417
00:24:30,183 --> 00:24:31,350
What did he seem like?

418
00:24:31,983 --> 00:24:34,550
Just decent and fine.

419
00:24:36,350 --> 00:24:37,350
What about Eun Ae?

420
00:24:38,283 --> 00:24:41,250
She said she'd stop by Cho Rong's
after working late.

421
00:24:42,450 --> 00:24:45,283
Mom, Dad,
I'm moving into the studio tomorrow.

422
00:24:46,050 --> 00:24:48,683
- Studio?
- Yeah, the company provided it.

423
00:24:49,583 --> 00:24:53,383
That's great.
The place is already cramped with you two.

424
00:24:53,850 --> 00:24:54,850
Are you using it alone?

425
00:24:54,850 --> 00:24:58,450
Well, mostly.

426
00:24:58,750 --> 00:25:01,683
Sometimes I'll have meetings
with the producer and other artists.

427
00:25:02,650 --> 00:25:04,250
Our daughter's doing well.

428
00:25:04,250 --> 00:25:06,083
They even gave you a studio.

429
00:25:06,550 --> 00:25:07,950
You're just realizing that now?

430
00:25:09,983 --> 00:25:14,550
But it's past dinner time,
and there's no sign of him.

431
00:25:15,550 --> 00:25:18,750
Should we invite him down to eat?
It's his first day here.

432
00:25:18,750 --> 00:25:20,250
Mom.

433
00:25:20,250 --> 00:25:22,883
That's an invasion of privacy. Leave it.

434
00:25:23,750 --> 00:25:24,850
- Really?
- Yeah.

435
00:25:25,150 --> 00:25:26,183
Still...

436
00:25:26,750 --> 00:25:29,450
Drumroll.

437
00:25:30,350 --> 00:25:31,350
How is it?

438
00:25:32,183 --> 00:25:33,483
It's spicy.

439
00:25:33,883 --> 00:25:36,583
That spicy? I toned it down.

440
00:25:37,483 --> 00:25:38,683
Don't you know I can't handle spice?

441
00:25:40,583 --> 00:25:44,150
Then I'll adjust it
to three levels next time. Got it.

442
00:25:49,550 --> 00:25:51,783
By the way, have you made any progress
with your team manager?

443
00:25:51,950 --> 00:25:55,350
Progress? Right, I didn't tell you.

444
00:25:55,950 --> 00:25:59,050
My team manager is that guy.
My first love.

445
00:26:00,550 --> 00:26:03,150
Your first love? The playground clover?

446
00:26:03,650 --> 00:26:05,083
(Hanyang Fresh Makgeolli)

447
00:26:05,783 --> 00:26:08,450
I think I'm going to give up.

448
00:26:10,050 --> 00:26:11,583
What, dieting?

449
00:26:12,250 --> 00:26:14,783
Have you even been listening?

450
00:26:16,250 --> 00:26:19,050
I really don't understand my feelings.

451
00:26:20,050 --> 00:26:21,850
When I think about him,

452
00:26:21,983 --> 00:26:24,550
my heart feels all warm...

453
00:26:25,150 --> 00:26:26,150
and tingly.

454
00:26:27,683 --> 00:26:31,150
And still, you're giving up...

455
00:26:31,150 --> 00:26:33,150
because that Manager Seo or whoever
liked him first?

456
00:26:33,783 --> 00:26:36,383
Is love first-come, first-served?

457
00:26:36,683 --> 00:26:39,450
If that's the case,
you were first. 25 years ago.

458
00:26:39,450 --> 00:26:41,150
I was five.

459
00:26:41,883 --> 00:26:43,650
And my team manager...

460
00:26:43,883 --> 00:26:47,183
is going back to the U.S.
after this project.

461
00:26:47,550 --> 00:26:50,983
You think you're being cool right now,
don't you?

462
00:26:51,350 --> 00:26:53,883
Is it cool to give up
before even starting?

463
00:26:54,050 --> 00:26:57,083
Then what do you want me to do? Confess?

464
00:26:57,550 --> 00:27:00,483
No, I can't. I won't.

465
00:27:03,283 --> 00:27:04,983
I do have an idea, though.

466
00:27:05,783 --> 00:27:06,850
You're drunk.

467
00:27:07,683 --> 00:27:10,150
Go to him like this...

468
00:27:10,483 --> 00:27:12,550
Go to him and?

469
00:27:13,950 --> 00:27:14,950
Make a move.

470
00:27:15,183 --> 00:27:16,683
What? Make a...

471
00:27:18,950 --> 00:27:21,550
What? She passed out.

472
00:27:22,050 --> 00:27:23,650
What should I do? Eun Ae?

473
00:27:46,983 --> 00:27:47,983
What is it?

474
00:28:01,350 --> 00:28:04,050
(Our Happy Days)

475
00:28:04,183 --> 00:28:06,450
This smells like the same perfume
Ms. Cho Eun Ae uses.

476
00:28:06,450 --> 00:28:07,750
It's the same shampoo we use at home.

477
00:28:07,750 --> 00:28:10,050
Do you use the same shampoo too?

478
00:28:10,050 --> 00:28:11,483
What are you talking about?

479
00:28:11,483 --> 00:28:14,350
I'm telling you to move out right now!

480
00:28:14,350 --> 00:28:17,350
So this is the studio we'll be sharing.

481
00:28:17,350 --> 00:28:19,450
I'll write, you draw.

482
00:28:19,450 --> 00:28:21,450
Let's respect each other's space.

483
00:28:21,450 --> 00:28:23,250
Can you spare some time after work?

484
00:28:23,783 --> 00:28:24,783
After work?

485
00:28:25,383 --> 00:28:26,983
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
